580, 5⁸1· agmina solvere: ‘they separated their battalions'3 i.e. they break up the three companies that were proceeding in column. terni: i.e. each of the three companies divides into bands or sections (chori), each com· prising one half, or six of the boys in the company. vocati: ‘being called,' i.e. by another signal from Epytides, they wheel and charge.
